    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Bonjour @francoischalifour \r\n\r\nThanks for you feedback. Here are my answers :\r\n\r\n- Yes the correct attribute is refined and the search results match what the user has selected. \r\n- The UI State format is alright but the value is not good when I console.log in the middleware. I get the previous value of the attribute. So the URL params are wrong and I'm not able to highlight the current category in my menu (as my code is based on the uistate value) \r\n- Yes,  I enabled the reactivity in my menu component whenever the uistate change in order to highlight the right category. ",
